track.strDescriptionEN:
"My House" is a song by American rapper Flo Rida from his 2015 EP My House. The song was released as the album's third official single on October 15, 2015 in the United States.

"My House" debuted at number ninety-six on the Billboard Hot 100 in the issue dated November 28, 2015, before falling to ninety-nine on the following week. The song then slowly gained momentum until a sharp increase in attention following Flo Rida's January 14th performance at The Tonight Show Starring Jimmy Fallon and halftime performance at the NFL match two days afterward, jumping places from 23–12 and becoming the track to gain the most digital sales in a week on the chart. Steep rises in performance continued as the song once again leaped to number five the following week with the issue dated February 9, 2016, becoming Flo Rida's seventh top 5 single in his native United States. The song has sold over 1 million copies.
